description:
The B.C Floods have devastated most of British Columbia and put a halt on supply chains. Rewind to summer of 2021, it was one of record-breaking heat and wildfires in British Columbia history. Months later, fall rains cascaded down mountain sides in torrents, triggering massive mudslides. Cities were cut off as bridges and highways were washed out. Store shelves quickly emptied as buyers rushed to hoard supplies. Is it even safe to live in the cities these days? Have you thought of living in the country? Should we be moving to the country? Does the Bible say anything about these things?
